FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1773349952
OL,3,CCornwall D-Day Veteran dies aged 101
OL,5,FWhen Mr Aldred was in Normandy, the
OL,6,FBritish tank advance had been halted
OL,7,Fby German Tiger Tanks. Speaking to ITV
OL,8,Fin 2023, he said: "The whole place had
OL,9,Fa ghastly smell of death and I am
OL,10,Fserious now, it was horrid.
OL,12,F"I was just a driver and I had to
OL,13,Fdrive this Cromwell. You must
OL,14,Funderstand that your visibility in a
OL,15,Ftank is seriously curtailed and you
OL,16,Fjust go where you are told to go.
OL,18,F"Each one has got his headset on and
OL,19,Fyou hear the orders: 'Go left, go
OL,20,Fleft. Put your foot down. Stop!'
OL,26,@tD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1773349952
OL,3,CCornwall D-Day Veteran dies aged 101
OL,5,F"And then you hear the order: 'Gunner,
OL,6,Ftraverse right. Fire at will.' And
OL,7,F'bang' and the smell of the gunpowder
OL,8,Fand the cordite in the tank and the
OL,9,Fslight apprehension I suppose that we
OL,10,Fare all under. It's a bit nerve-
OL,11,Fwracking you know but you don't let
OL,12,Fyour mates down."
OL,14,FAt Bourneville-Sainte-Croix, Mr
OL,15,FAldred's tank took a direct hit from a
OL,16,FGerman tank. The shot struck the
OL,17,Fvehicle's gearbox which brought the
OL,18,FBritish tank to a halt.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1773349952
OL,3,CCornwall D-Day Veteran dies aged 101
OL,5,FMr Aldred said: "I felt the thump as
OL,6,Fit hit us. It was a terrible thump.
OL,7,FAlways remember that. And the next
OL,8,Fthing I heard was 'bail out' and I
OL,9,Fwent through that hatch like a
OL,10,Fjackrabbit. Dear, oh dear. All of us
OL,11,Fgot out."
OL,13,FPaying tribute to Mr Aldred, a
OL,14,Fspokesperson for British Normandy
OL,15,FMemorial said: "We are very sad to
OL,16,Fshare that Normandy Veteran Richard
OL,17,FAldred has passed away at the weekend
OL,18,Faged 101.
OL,26,@sD@IO]wD@POU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/5
